Louis Vuitton has launched its new premium smartwatch, the Tambour Horizon. The device is produced with assistance from Qualcomm and Google, and runs the Android Wear 2.0 operating system. The hardware inside the stylised chassis includes a 1.2-inch AMOLED touch display (390 x 390) and 300mAh battery. It is compatible with Android and iOS smartphones, sports Bluetooth and Wi-Fi connectivity, and includes a 2-year warranty. Louis Vuitton’s Tambour Horizon is also water resistant to 30 metres and will last 22 hours on a single charge. The device is available in various colour options – priced from $2,450 for the gray and brown models, and $2,900 for the black version.   